Palace railway station|Crystal Palace]] \n*[[Penge West railway station|Penge West]]\n\nNational Rail stations:\n*[[Birkbeck station|Birkbeck]]\n*[[Beckenham Junction railway station|Beckenham Junction]]\n*[[Shortlands railway station|Shortlands]]\n*[[Bromley North railway station|Bromley North]]\n*[[Bromley South railway station|Bromley South]]\n*[[St Mary Cray railway station|St Mary Cray]]\n*[[Sundridge Park railway station|Sundridge Park]]\n*[[Ravensbourne railway station|Ravensbourne]]\n*[[Bickley railway station|Bickley]]\n*[[Elmstead Woods railway station|Elmstead Woods]]\n*[[Chislehurst railway station|Chislehurst]]\n*[[Petts Wood railway station|Petts Wood]]\n*[[Orpington railway station|Orpington]]\n*[[Chelsfield railway station|Chelsfield]]\n*[[Knockholt railway station|Knockholt]]\n*[[Kent House railway station|Kent House]]\n*[[Penge East railway station|Penge East]]\n*[[Lower Sydenham railway station|Lower Sydenham]] (Shared with [[London Borough of Lewisham|Lewisham]])\n*[[New Beckenham railway station|New Beckenham]]\n*[[Clock House railway station|Clock House]]\n*[[Elmers End station|Elmers End]]\n*[[Eden Park railway station|Eden Park]]\n*[[West Wickham railway station|West Wickham]]\n*[[Hayes railway station|Hayes]]\n\nTramlink stops:\n*[[Beckenham Junction railway station|Beckenham Junction]]\n*[[Beckenham Road tram stop|Beckenham Road]]\n*[[Avenue Road tram stop|Avenue Road]]\n*[[Birkbeck station|Birkbeck]]\n*[[Elmers End station|Elmers End]]\n\nIn March 2011, the main forms of transport that residents used to travel to work were: driving a car or van, 27.4% of all residents aged 16\u201374; train, 5.1%; bus, minibus or coach, 5.1%; on foot, 4.3%; work mainly at or from home, 4.0%; underground, metro, light rail, tram, 2.3%; passenger in a car or van, 1.5%.<ref>{{cite web|title=2011 Census: QS701EW Method of travel to work, local authorities in England and Wales|url=http://www.ons.gov.uk/ons/rel/census/2011-census/key-statistics-and-quick-statistics-for-wards-and-output-areas-in-england-and-wales/rft-qs701ew.xls|publisher=Office for National Statistics|accessdate=23 November 2013|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130915043538/http://www.ons.gov.uk/ons/rel/census/2011-census/key-statistics-and-quick-statistics-for-wards-and-output-areas-in-england-and-wales/rft-qs701ew.xls|archivedate=15 September 2013|df=dmy-all}} Percentages are of all residents aged 16-74 including those not in employment. Respondents could only pick one mode, specified as the journey\u2019s longest part by distance.</ref>\n\n==Sport, leisure and culture==\nThe Borough has several sporting clubs:\n*[[Bromley F.C.]] a [[Non-League football]] club\n*[[Cray Wanderers F.C.]] a [[Non-League football]] club\n*[[Orpington F.C.]] a [[Non-League football]] club\n*[[Holmesdale F.C.]] a [[Non-League football]] club\n*[[Greenwich Borough F.C.]] a [[Non-League football]] club\n*[[Beckenham Town F.C.]] a [[Non-League football]] club\n*Club Langley FC a [[Non-League football]] club\n\nThe borough is also home to an extensive [[Bromley Borough Libraries Service|libraries service]], containing 14 branches,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bromley.gov.uk/info/200062/libraries|title=Libraries|website=London Borough of Bromley}}</ref> currently operated by [[Greenwich Leisure Limited]] under their trademark Better on behalf of Bromley council.\n\nThe Beckenham Comedy Cabaret,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://en-gb.facebook.com/beckenhamcomedycabaret/|title=Beckenham Comedy Cabaret|website=Facebook page for Beckenham Comedy Cabaret}}{{Dead link|date=March 2020 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> a monthly comedy cabaret event, hosted and run by Jody Kamali, has been running in the heart of [[Beckenham]] since 2015, usually on the last Friday evening of the month.\n\n==London Fire Brigade==\n[[London Fire Brigade]] has four fire stations within the London Borough of Bromley. The borough is the largest in the city: about 150&nbsp;km<sup>2</sup>. With just one pumping appliance, Orpington has one of the largest areas to cover in London, measuring 46.7&nbsp;km<sup>2</sup>. In 2006/2007, Orpington attended 1,308 incidents. There is also a high volume pump at the station. Beckenham, Bromley and Biggin Hill cover the rest of the borough with four pumping appliances and a hose layer.<ref name=\"london-fire\">{{cite web |url=http://www.london-fire.gov.uk/about_us/media/Bromley.pdf |title=London Fire Brigade - Bromley Profile |accessdate=6 February 2016 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080530154651/http://www.london-fire.gov.uk/about_us/media/Bromley.pdf |archivedate=30 May 2008 |df=dmy-all |date=9 August 2007 |website=[[London Fire Brigade]] }}</ref>\n\nIn 2006/2007 just under 4000 incidents were attended in the borough. Noticeably, compared to 2005/2006 there was an 11% decrease in special service calls (road traffic collisions, chemical incidents, flooding etc.).<ref name=\"london-fire\" />\n\n==Twin Towns==\nBromley is [[town twinning|twinned]] with:\n*{{Flagicon|Germany}} [[Neuwied]], [[Rhineland-Palatinate]], Germany.\n\n==See also==\n{{Portal|London}}\n*[[Bromley parks and open spaces]]\n*[[List of churches in the London Borough of Bromley]]\n\n==References==\n;References\n{{Reflist}}\n;Notes\n{{Reflist|group=n}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.ideal-homes.org.uk/bromley/ Summary of formation of the Borough, including its constituent parts]\n*[http://www.bromley.gov.uk London Borough of Bromley council website]\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20051231054233/http://www.bromley.gov.uk/leisure/museums/bromley_museum.htm London Borough of Bromley Museum]\n*[http://www.communitylinksbromley.org.uk/ Council for Voluntary Service for the London Borough of Bromley]\n*[http://bromley-cleaner.co.uk/ Directory of local services]\n*[http://www.beckenhamhistory.co.uk/ Images of Bromley]\n*[http://www.BromleyNWA.org.uk/ Bromley Neighbourhood Watch Association website (BromleyNWA.org.uk)]\n\n{{LB Bromley}}\n{{London}}\n\n{{Coord|51|20|N|0|05|E|region:GB_type:adm1st|display=title}}\n\n{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2011}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:London Borough Of Bromley}}\n[[Category:London boroughs|Bromley]]\n[[Category:London Borough of Bromley| ]]\n[[Category:1965 establishments in the United Kingdom]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use British English|date=August 2015}}\n{{Infobox settlement\n<!-- See Template:Infobox settlement for additional fields and descriptions -->\n| name                    = <!-- at least one of the first two fields must be filled in -->\n| official_name            = London Borough of Bromley\n| other_name              = \n| settlement_type         = [[London boroughs|Borough]]\n<!-- transliteration(s) -------->\n<!-- images, nickname, motto --->\n| image_skyline           = \n| imagesize               = 270px\n| image_alt               = \n| image_caption           = \n| image_shield            = Arms-bromley-lb.jpg\n| shield_size             = 100px\n| shield_alt              = \n| shield_link             = Coat of arms of the London Borough of Bromley\n| image_blank_emblem      = Lb bromley.svg\n| blank_emblem_type       = Council logo\n| blank_emblem_size       = 100px\n| blank_emblem_alt        = \n| blank_emblem_link       = \n| motto                   = \n<!-- maps and coordinates ------>\n| image_map               = LondonBromley.svg\n| map_alt                 = \n| map_caption             = Bromley shown within [[Greater London]]\n| coor_pinpoint           = <!-- to specify exact location of coordinates (was coor_type) -->\n| coordinates       = \n| coordinates_footnotes   = <!-- for references: use <ref> tags -->\n<!-- location ------------------>\n| subdivision_type        = [[List of sovereign states|Sovereign state]]\n| subdivision_name        = [[United Kingdom]]\n| subdivision_type2       = [[Country of the United Kingdom|Constituent country]]\n| subdivision_name2       = [[England]]\n| subdivision_type3       = [[Regions of England|Region]]\n| subdivision_name3       = [[Greater London|London]]\n| subdivision_type4       = [[Ceremonial counties of England|Ceremonial county]]\n| subdivision_name4       = [[Greater London]]\n| subdivision_type5       = \n| subdivision_name5       = \n| established_title       = Created\n| established_date        = 1 April 1965\n| established_title1      = \n| established_date1       = \n| named_for               = \n<!-- seat, smaller parts -->\n| seat_type               = Admin HQ\n| seat                    = Stockwell Close, Bromley\n<!-- government type, leaders -->\n| government_footnotes    = <!-- for references: use <ref> tags -->\n| government_type         = [[London boroughs|London borough council]]\n| governing_body          = [[Bromley London Borough Council]]\n| leader_party            = {{English district control|ONS=00AF|GSS=E09000006}}\n| leader_title            = Leadership\n| leader_name             = Leader & Cabinet\n| leader_title1           = Mayor\n| leader_name1            = [[Nicholas Bennett]]\n| leader_title2           = London&nbsp;Assembly\n| leader_name2            = [[Gareth Bacon]] (Conservative) AM for [[Bexley and Bromley (London Assembly constituency)|Bexley and Bromley]]\n| leader_title3           = [[List of MPs elected in the 2010 United Kingdom general election|MPs]]\n| leader_name3            = [[Gareth Bacon]] (Conservative) <br>[[Bob Stewart (politician)|Bob Stewart]] (Conservative) <br>[[Bob Neill]] (Conservative) <br>[[Ellie Reeves]] (Labour) <br>\n| leader_title4           = EU Parliament\n| leader_name4            = [[London (European Parliament constituency)|London]]\n<!-- display settings  --------->\n| total_type              = <!-- to set a non-standard label for total area and population rows -->\n| unit_pref               = <!-- enter: Imperial, to display imperial before metric -->\n<!-- area ---------------------->\n| area_footnotes          = <!-- for references: use <ref> tags -->\n| area_magnitude          = <!-- use only to set a special wikilink -->\n| area_total_km2          = 150.15\n| area_total_sq_mi        = <!-- see table @ Template:Infobox settlement for details -->\n| area_total_dunam        = <!-- used in Middle East articles only -->\n| area_land_km2           = \n| area_land_sq_mi         = \n| area_water_km2          = \n| area_water_sq_mi        = \n| area_water_percent      = \n| area_urban_footnotes    = <!-- for references: use <ref> tags -->\n| area_urban_km2          = \n| area_urban_sq_mi        = \n| area_rural_footnotes    = <!-- for references: use <ref> tags -->\n| area_rural_km2          = \n| area_rural_sq_mi        = \n| area_metro_footnotes    = <!-- for references: use <ref> tags -->\n| area_metro_km2          = \n| area_metro_sq_mi        = \n| area_rank               = {{English district area rank|ONS=00AF|GSS=E09000006}} [[List of English districts by area|(of {{English district total}})]]\n| area_blank1_title       = \n| area_blank1_km2         = \n| area_blank1_sq_mi       = \n| area_blank2_title       = \n| area_blank2_km2         = \n| area_blank2_sq_mi       = \n<!-- population ---------------->\n| population_footnotes    = <!-- for references: use <ref> tags -->\n| population_total        = {{English district population|ONS=00AF|GSS=E09000006}}\n| population_as_of        = {{United Kingdom statistics year}}\n| population_rank         = {{English district rank|ONS=00AF|GSS=E09000006}} [[List of English districts by population|(of {{English district total}})]]\n| population_density_km2  = auto\n| population_density_sq_mi= \n| population_blank1_title = Ethnicity<ref name=LBEthnicPercentages>''[http://www.ons.gov.uk/ons/rel/census/2011-census/key-statistics-for-local-authorities-in-england-and-wales/rft-table-ks201ew.xls 2011 Census: Ethnic group, local authorities in England and Wales]'', [[Office for National Statistics]] (2012). See [[Classification of ethnicity in the United Kingdom]] for the full descriptions used