 is the extension of the Bakerloo Line, but would not be scheduled to begin till 2040, if accepted.\n\nStations operated by [[London Overground]] (all are also served by [[Southern (Govia Thameslink Railway)|Southern]]):\n*[[Anerley railway station|Anerley]]\n*[[Crystal Palace railway station|Crystal Palace]] \n*[[Penge West railway station|Penge West]]\n\nNational Rail stations:\n*[[Birkbeck station|Birkbeck]]\n*[[Beckenham Junction railway station|Beckenham Junction]]\n*[[Shortlands railway station|Shortlands]]\n*[[Bromley North railway station|Bromley North]]\n*[[Bromley South railway station|Bromley South]]\n*[[St Mary Cray railway station|St Mary Cray]]\n*[[Sundridge Park railway station|Sundridge Park]]\n*[[Ravensbourne railway station|Ravensbourne]]\n*[[Bickley railway station|Bickley]]\n*[[Elmstead Woods railway station|Elmstead Woods]]\n*[[Chislehurst railway station|Chislehurst]]\n*[[Petts Wood railway station|Petts Wood]]\n*[[Orpington railway station|Orpington]]\n*[[Chelsfield railway station|Chelsfield]]\n*[[Knockholt railway station|Knockholt]]\n*[[Kent House railway station|Kent House]]\n*[[Penge East railway station|Penge East]]\n*[[Lower Sydenham railway station|Lower Sydenham]] (Shared with [[London Borough of Lewisham|Lewisham]])\n*[[New Beckenham railway station|New Beckenham]]\n*[[Clock House railway station|Clock House]]\n*[[Elmers End station|Elmers End]]\n*[[Eden Park railway station|Eden Park]]\n*[[West Wickham railway station|West Wickham]]\n*[[Hayes railway station|Hayes]]\n\nTramlink stops:\n*[[Beckenham Junction railway station|Beckenham Junction]]\n*[[Beckenham Road tram stop|Beckenham Road]]\n*[[Avenue Road tram stop|Avenue Road]]\n*[[Birkbeck station|Birkbeck]]\n*[[Elmers End station|Elmers End]]\n\nIn March 2011, the main forms of transport that residents used to travel to work were: driving a car or van, 27.4% of all residents aged 16\u201374; train, 5.1%; bus, minibus or coach, 5.1%; on foot, 4.3%; work mainly at or from home, 4.0%; underground, metro, light rail, tram, 2.3%; passenger in a car or van, 1.5%.<ref>{{cite web|title=2011 Census: QS701EW Method of travel to work, local authorities in England and Wales|url=http://www.ons.gov.uk/ons/rel/census/2011-census/key-statistics-and-quick-statistics-for-wards-and-output-areas-in-england-and-wales/rft-qs701ew.xls|publisher=Office for National Statistics|accessdate=23 November 2013|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130915043538/http://www.ons.gov.uk/ons/rel/census/2011-census/key-statistics-and-quick-statistics-for-wards-and-output-areas-in-england-and-wales/rft-qs701ew.xls|archivedate=15 September 2013|df=dmy-all}} Percentages are of all residents aged 16-74 including those not in employment. Respondents could only pick one mode, specified as the journey\u2019s longest part by distance.</ref>\n\n==Sport, leisure and culture==\nThe Borough has several sporting clubs:\n*[[Bromley F.C.]] a [[Non-League football]] club\n*[[Cray Wanderers F.C.]] a [[Non-League football]] club\n*[[Orpington F.C.]] a [[Non-League football]] club\n*[[Holmesdale F.C.]] a [[Non-League football]] club\n*[[Greenwich Borough F.C.]] a [[Non-League football]] club\n*[[Beckenham Town F.C.]] a [[Non-League football]] club\n*Club Langley FC a [[Non-League football]] club\n\nThe borough is also home to an extensive [[Bromley Borough Libraries Service|libraries service]], containing 14 branches,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bromley.gov.uk/info/200062/libraries|title=Libraries|website=London Borough of Bromley}}</ref> currently operated by [[Greenwich Leisure Limited]] under their trademark Better on behalf of Bromley council.\n\nThe Beckenham Comedy Cabaret,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://en-gb.facebook.com/beckenhamcomedycabaret/|title=Beckenham Comedy Cabaret|website=Facebook page for Beckenham Comedy Cabaret}}{{Dead link|date=March 2020 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> a monthly comedy cabaret event, hosted and run by Jody Kamali, has been running in the heart of [[Beckenham]] since 2015, usually on the last Friday evening of the month.\n\n==London Fire Brigade==\n[[London Fire Brigade]] has four fire stations within the London Borough of Bromley. The borough is the largest in the city: about 150&nbsp;km<sup>2</sup>. With just one pumping appliance, Orpington has one of the largest areas to cover in London, measuring 46.7&nbsp;km<sup>2</sup>. In 2006/2007, Orpington attended 1,308 incidents. There is also a high volume pump at the station. Beckenham, Bromley and Biggin Hill cover the rest of the borough with four pumping appliances and a hose layer.<ref name=\"london-fire\">{{cite web |url=http://www.london-fire.gov.uk/about_us/media/Bromley.pdf |title=London Fire Brigade - Bromley Profile |accessdate=6 February 2016 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080530154651/http://www.london-fire.gov.uk/about_us/media/Bromley.pdf |archivedate=30 May 2008 |df=dmy-all |date=9 August 2007 |website=[[London Fire Brigade]] }}</ref>\n\nIn 2006/2007 just under 4000 incidents were attended in the borough. Noticeably, compared to 2005/2006 there was an 11% decrease in special service calls (road traffic collisions, chemical incidents, flooding etc.).<ref name=\"london-fire\" />\n\n==Twin Towns==\nBromley is [[town twinning|twinned]] with:\n*{{Flagicon|Germany}} [[Neuwied]], [[Rhineland-Palatinate]], Germany.\n\n==See also==\n{{Portal|London}}\n*[[Bromley parks and open spaces]]\n*[[List of churches in the London Borough of Bromley]]\n\n==References==\n;References\n{{Reflist}}\n;Notes\n{{Reflist|group=n}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.ideal-homes.org.uk/bromley/ Summary of formation of the Borough, including its constituent parts]\n*[http://www.bromley.gov.uk London Borough of Bromley council website]\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20051231054233/http://www.bromley.gov.uk/leisure/museums/bromley_museum.htm London Borough of Bromley Museum]\n*[http://www.communitylinksbromley.org.uk/ Council for Voluntary Service for the London Borough of Bromley]\n*[http://bromley-cleaner.co.uk/ Directory of local services]\n*[http://www.beckenhamhistory.co.uk/ Images of Bromley]\n*[http://www.BromleyNWA.org.uk/ Bromley Neighbourhood Watch Association website (BromleyNWA.org.uk)]\n\n{{LB Bromley}}\n{{London}}\n\n{{Coord|51|20|N|0|05|E|region:GB_type:adm1st|display=title}}\n\n{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2011}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:London Borough Of Bromley}}\n[[Category:London boroughs|Bromley]]\n[[Category:London Borough of Bromley| ]]\n[[Category:1965 establishments in the United Kingdom]]\n", "name_user": "2a02:c7d:ce0:2600:cd56:5d02:9bc8:1150", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(\u2192\u200eGeography)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/London_Borough_of_Bromley"}
{"title_page": "Killer Women", "text_new": "{{short description|American crime drama television series}}\n{{Infobox television\n| show_name            = Killer Women\n| image                = Killer Women.jpg\n| genre                = [[Crime drama]]\n| based_on             = ''[[Mujeres Asesinas (Argentina)|Mujeres Asesinas]]''\n| developer            = Hannah Shakespeare\n| starring             = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Tricia Helfer]]\n* [[Marc Blucas]]\n* [[Alex Fernandez (actor)|Alex Fernandez]]\n* [[Marta Milans]]\n* [[Michael Trucco]]\n}}\n| theme_music_composer = \n| opentheme            = \n| composer             = Mark Kilian \n| country              = United States\n| language             = English\n| num_seasons          = 1\n| num_episodes         = 12\n| list_episodes        = #Episodes\n| executive_producer   =  {{Plainlist|\n* Hannah Shakespeare\n* [[Sof\u00eda Vergara]]\n* [[Ben Silverman]]\n* Luis Balaguer\n* [[Martin Campbell]]\n}}\n| producer             =\n| location             = \n| camera               =\n| runtime              = 42 minutes\n| company              = {{Plainlist|\n*[[Electus]]\n*LatinWE\n*[[ABC Studios]]\n}}\n| distributor          = [[Disney\u2013ABC Domestic Television]]\n| network              = [[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]]\n| picture_format       =\n| audio_format         =\n| first_aired          = {{Start date|2014|1|7}}\n| last_aired           = {{End date|2014|3|25}}<ref name=\"Renewed and Canceled\"/>\n| related              = ''[[Mujeres Asesinas (Argentina)|Mujeres asesinas]] (Argentina)''<br />''[[Mujeres asesinas (Mexican TV series)|Mujeres asesinas]] (Mexico)''\n| status               = \n| website              = \n| website_title        = Official website\n| production_website   = \n}}\n\n'''''Killer Women''''' is an American [[crime drama]] television series that aired on [[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] from January 7 to March 25, 2014. The series is based on the [[Argentina|Argentine]] crime drama ''[[Mujeres Asesinas (Argentina)|Mujeres Asesinas]]'', which was adapted into an American setting by writer Hannah Shakespeare. Shakespeare also serves as an executive producer alongside [[Sof\u00eda Vergara]], [[Ben Silverman]], Luis Balaguer, and [[Martin Campbell]] for [[Pol-ka|Pol-Ka Productions]], Silverman's Electus Productions, Vergara and Balaguer's Latin World Entertainment, and [[ABC Studios]].<ref name=\"ewp\">{{cite web|url=http://insidetv.ew.com/2013/05/10/abc-renews-nashville-scandal-greys-anatomy-and-castle|title=ABC renews 'Nashville,' 'Scandal, 'Grey's Anatomy' and more|last=Rice|first=Lynette|work=Entertainment Weekly|date=May 10, 2013|accessdate=May 11, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2013/tv/news/abcs-first-new-series-order-goes-to-agents-of-shield-1200479556|title=ABC Orders 7 Dramas and 5 Comedies, Axes 'Happy Endings'|last=Littleton|first=Cynthia|work=Variety|date=May 10, 2013|accessdate=May 11, 2013}}</ref> The series stars [[Tricia Helfer]].<ref name=helfer>{{cite web|url=http://www.tvfanatic.com/2013/05/tricia-helfer-talks-lifetime-movie-playing-a-killer-woman-on-abc/|title=Tricia Helfer Talks Lifetime Movie, Playing a Killer Woman on ABC|last=Halterman|first=Jim|work=TV Fanatic|date=May 11, 2013|accessdate=May 17, 2013}}</ref> The pilot episode was directed by [[Lawrence Trilling]].<ref name=\"thefutoncritic\">{{cite web|url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/devwatch/killer-women|title=KILLER WOMEN (ABC)|work=The Futon Critic|accessdate=May 11, 2013}}</ref>\n\nOn May 9, 2014, ABC canceled ''Killer Women'' after only one season.<ref name=\"Renewed and Canceled\">{{cite web|url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2014/05/09/list-of-renewed-and-cancelled-broadcast-shows-for-the-2013-14-broadcast-season/261970/|title=List of Renewed and Cancelled Broadcast Shows for the 2013\u201314 Broadcast Season|last=Seidman|first=Robert|publisher=TV by the Numbers|date=May 9, 2014|accessdate=May 10, 2014}}</ref>\n\n==Premise==\nThe series follows the life of Molly Parker, a former beauty queen and daughter of a sheriff who is recently separated from her abusive State Senator husband. She rises to the top ranks of one of the most elite and male-dominated law enforcement establishments, the [[Texas Ranger Division|Texas Rangers]]. The perpetrators of the episodic crimes she solves are all female.\n\n==Cast and characters==\n\n===Main cast===\n*[[Tricia Helfer]]<ref name=helfer/> as Molly Parker, a Texas Ranger<ref name=\"thefutoncritic\"/>\n*[[Marc Blucas]] as Dan Winston, a DEA agent and Molly's love interest<ref name=\"thefutoncritic\"/>\n*[[Alex Fernandez (actor)|Alex Fernandez]] as Luis Zea, Molly's boss<ref name=\"thefutoncritic\"/>\n*[[Michael Trucco]] as Billy Parker, Molly's brother<ref name=\"thefutoncritic\"/>\n*[[Marta Milans]] as Becca Parker, Billy's wife<ref name=\"thefutoncritic\"/>\n\n===Guest stars===\n*[[Nadine Velazquez]] as Martina Alvarez\n*[[Beth Riesgraf]] as Jennifer Jennings<ref name=\"thefutoncritic\"/>\n*[[Melora Hardin]] as Nan Reed\n*[[Jeffrey Nordling]] as Jake Colton\n*Vincent Fuentes as Paco La Mosca\n*Paul Howard Smith as Sherriff Lloyd Watkins\n*[[Aisha Hinds]] as FBI Agent Linda Clark\n*Peyton McDavitt as Andrea Corbett\n*[[Paola Turbay]] as Carmen Garza\n*[[Alexandra Pomales]] as Hailee Parker\n*[[Michael Shamus Wiles]] as Colt Ritter\n*[[Arlin Alcala]] as Nurse Sanchez\n\n==Episodes==\n{{Episode table |total_width=99; |background=#9A0700 |overall= |title= |director= |writer= |airdate= |viewers= |country=U.S. |episodes=\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = 1\n| Title = La Sicaria\n| DirectedBy = [[Lawrence Trilling]]\n| WrittenBy = Hannah Shakespeare\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2014|1|7}}\n| Viewers = 3.96<ref name=\"1.01\">{{cite web|url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2014/01/08/tuesday-final-ratings-marvels-agents-of-s-h-i-e-l-d-ncis-trophy-wife-adjusted-down/227699|title=Tuesday Final Ratings: 'Marvel's Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D.', 'NCIS' & 'Chicago Fire' Adjusted Up; 'Trophy Wife' Adjusted Down|last=Bibel|first=Sara|work=TV by the Numbers|date=January 8, 2013|accessdate=January 8, 2013}}</ref>\n| ShortSummary = When Martina Alvarez ([[Nadine Velazquez]]) shoots and kills an ADA on her wedding day, it appears to be a case of jealous rage, until Texas Ranger Molly Parker finds several elements of Martina's story that don't add up. Molly also discovers from her new love interest, DEA agent Dan Winston, that the DEA had an upcoming meeting scheduled with the ADA. Meanwhile, Molly tries to get her estranged husband, State Senator Jake Colton, to sign divorce papers, which he's refused to do for over six months.\n| LineColor = 9A0700\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = 2\n| Title = Some Men Need Killing\n| DirectedBy = Marc Roskin\n| WrittenBy = Hannah Shakespeare\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2014|1|14}}\n| Viewers = 3.51<ref name=\"1.02\">{{cite web|url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2014/01/15/tuesday-final-ratings-the-mindy-project-adjusted-down-no-adjustment-for-chicago-fire-or-brooklyn-nine-nine/229530|title=Tuesday Final Ratings: 'The Mindy Project' Adjusted Down; No Adjustment for 'Chicago Fire' or 'Brooklyn Nine-Nine'|last=Kondolojy|first=Amanda|work=TV by the Numbers|date=January 15, 2014|accessdate=January 15, 2014}}</ref>\n| ShortSummary = A wealthy water park owner is murdered by a professional hitman at a function that Molly and Dan are attending, and suspicion falls on the man's wife, Nan ([[Melora Hardin]]), when Molly discovers that he controlled every aspect of her life. But after Nan reveals that the hitman approached her, not the other way around, Molly finds a common thread connecting this murder to similar killings\u2014just in time for Molly to save her abusive husband Jake from becoming the next victim. Becca suspects that Billy has been cheating, as he keeps running out at night.\n| LineColor = 9A0700\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = 3\n| Title = Warrior\n| DirectedBy = [[Martha Coolidge]]\n| W